ac-calendar-2.png" alt=3D"" class=3D"wp-image-115" width=3D"100%" height=3D=
"auto"></figure>



<p>Don=E2=80=99t forget that Chinese New Year doesn=E2=80=99t fall on 1 Jan=
uary. If you are born in January or February, just check when Chinese New Y=
ear fell during the year you were born to ensure you have aligned the corre=
ct year with your birth.</p>



